format: A data frame with 46 observations on the following 15 variables.

parameters.medfaminc: A county-level estimate for the median family income
parameters.population: An estimate of the county-level population
parameters.percapinc: A county-level estimate for per capita income
parameters.sanders: Bernie Sanders' county-level vote share in the 2016 party primary
parameters.unemployment: Unemployment rate for the county for January 2016
parameters.romneyshare2012: Mitt Romney's vote share at the county-level from the 2012 general election
parameters.trump: Donald Trump's county-level vote share in the 2016 party primary
parameters.illiteracy: An estimate of the percent of the county lacking "basic" prose literacy skills
parameters.rubio: Marco Rubio's county-level vote share in the 2016 party primary
parameters.medhouseinc: A county-level estimate for the median household income
parameters.cruz: Ted Cruz' county-level vote share in the 2016 party primary
parameters.clinton: Hillary Clinton's county-level vote share in the 2016 party primary
parameters.perblack: Percentage of the county that is black
parameters.perhsgrad: Percentage of the county whose residents 25 years and older have at least a high school education

reference:
The illiteracy estimate comes from a Department of Education report from 2003.
The unemployment rate data come from the Bureau of Labor Statistics. A Github repository contains
more information: https://github.com/svmiller/sc-primary-2016.
title: South Carolina County GOP/Democratic Primary Data, 2016
description:
Description
County-level data on vote share and various background/demographic
information for the 2016 South Carolina GOP/Democratic primaries.
